
VARIABLE DANSC

Number 2387
Name Phantom Vale
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The air is thick with the scent of cherry blossoms, so wonderfully rich
and heady that you can hardly think of anything else. Grass so green that
it can't possibly be real springs up when you lift your feet after each
step, uncrushed and unbroken. Water so clear that it sighs rather than
the babbling course of a more normal brook runs through the center of the
peaceful vale, glowing in the light of an alien sun. The wheel which hovers
in the air beside it is a gate of sorts, leading to the mortal realm.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 426
EXIT NE 2388
;
Number 2388
Name Phantom Vale
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
Verdant and fresh, the grass forms a path beside the stream, leading on
upstream to the source of the magical current. Just across the water you
see the cherry trees, each one resplendent with white blossoms, petals
falling slowly with each touch of the wind like a fragrant snowfall in
the summer air. Fruit hangs from the end of each spreading branch, low
enough to be in reach for those at the base of the trunks.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 426
IFPREVERB GO 0
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You gently pick your way across the gentle, peaceful stream.
        ECHO OTHERS %N crosses the beautiful stream.
        DISBAND
        MOVE 2390
ENDIF
EXIT SW 2387
EXIT NW 2389
;
Number 2389
Name Phantom Vale
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
A familiar arch guards the entrance to the phantom vale, pulled from
the stone of this dreaming world to form a portal between the astral
regions. Over the stream, around the bend in its shining waters, you
can still see the cherry trees, no longer raining their petals down
so quickly in the changing breeze. They still seem remarkably inviting.
The stream itself flows from one side of the arch, allowing plenty of
room not only for a human but for an entire dragon to pass through,
and now you see that there is one difference between this one and that
at the village of the Korvatae- it was shaped to accomodate dragons.
*DESCRIPTION_END
